homestead capital closes oversubscribed fund ii at  million  business wire homestead capital closes oversubscribed fund ii at  million november    am eastern standard time san franciscobusiness wirehomestead capital usa llc “homestead” a private equity firm investing in operating farmland in the united states has held a final close of its second fund homestead capital usa farmland fund ii lp “fund ii” at its hard cap of  million in limited partner capital commitments surpassing an original fundraising target of  million and more than doubling the size of its debut fund “we are very pleased with the support we received from returning investors and the quality of new limited partners that we were able to attract to fund ii our investor base spans a broad range of partners including public pension funds endowments foundations insurance companies and fundoffunds” said gabe santos a cofounder and portfolio manager of homestead dan little also a cofounder and portfolio manager of homestead added “with the capital from fund ii we plan to continue to execute on our valueadd investment strategy because of our local presence and broad agricultural network we are seeing many attractive investment opportunities in our targeted regions” like its predecessor fund homestead capital usa farmland fund i lp which owns a portfolio of farms across  states producing  different crops homestead will continue its focus on making row and permanent crop farmland investments in the mountain west pacific midwest and delta regions homestead applies a bottomup approach to its investment decisions and management by identifying opportunities to create value and is committed to preserving the value of farmland over the long term by adhering to sustainable farm management practices homestead also applies a topdown overlay to portfolio construction and risk management in an effort to ensure proper diversification and an appropriate risk and reward profile homestead was represented by kirkland  ellis llp as fund counsel and did not use a placement agent about homestead capital homestead capital is a private equity firm investing in operating farmland across the mountain west pacific midwest and delta regions of the united states with offices in council bluffs iowa and san francisco california homestead has a vertically integrated investment platform led by a team of professionals with deep agricultural and financial experience in investing farm management farm acquisition portfolio construction and risk management for more information please visit the company website at httpwwwhomesteadcapitalcom contacts homestead capitalaleah dawson  contacts homestead capitalaleah dawson  search advanced news search advanced news search log in sign up homestead capital – local insight national presence local insight national presence we are  an investment firm focused on acquiring diversified farmland assets in the united states welcome to homestead capital homestead capital is a private investment partnership formed exclusively to invest in operating farmland across the mountain west delta midwest and pacific regions of the united states with offices in council bluffs iowa and san francisco california homestead has a vertically integrated investment platform led by a team of professionals with deep agricultural and financial experience in investing farm management farm acquisition portfolio construction and risk management homestead’s local presence experience and knowledge form the basis of its bottomup approach to sourcing underwriting and managing its farmland assets compelling opportunity diversified investment strategy cohesive team it’s not about what we do it’s about who we are contact – homestead capital contact homecontact get in touch we are here to answer any questions you may have about our services and experiences reach out to us and we’ll respond as soon as we can fund headquarters  mission street suite  san francisco ca  infohomesteadcapitalcom farm management headquarters  e graham ave council bluffs iowa  infohomesteadcapitalcom send us a message your message about – homestead capital about homeabout who we are homestead capital usa farmland fund i received support from a diverse range of leading institutional investors the majority of which are pension funds endowments and foundations and also include funds of funds high net worth individuals and insurance companies the fund intends to acquire farm investments in the mountain west pacific midwest and delta regions and construct a diversified portfolio of assets across those regions crops lease types farm operators and certain other risk factors demand for the fund reflects growing investor interest in farmland as an asset class and the opportunity it offers to produce attractive riskadjusted returns and act as a portfolio diversifier and hedge against inflation leadership daniel littlecofounderportfolio manager gabe santoscofounderportfolio manager gary thien afm araportfolio manager head of farm management and due diligence team alex sauervice presidentpermanent crops tony windhamvice president row crops ryan gallantinvestment associate peter suskochief financial officer andrea davidsonfinance director controller jess vilsackoutsourced general counsel aleah dawsonoffice administrator project manager regional farm managers darrell atkinson afm aacregional farm manager pacific region richard brockmeyerregional farm manager pacific region stephen brunson afmregional farm manager delta region george baird afmregional farm manager delta region ray brownfield alc afmregional farm manager midwest region thomas boyer aac afm araregional farm manager mountainwest region brandon viningregional farm manager mountainwest region carrie gibsonregional farm manager mountain west region larry wrightregional farm manager mountain west region about – homestead capital about homeabout who we are homestead capital usa farmland fund i received support from a diverse range of leading inst