th more than half a century of combined investment acquisition and asset management experience” explained gabe santos managing partner and head of acquisitions and structuring at homestead “our local networks and national scope allow us to employ a bottomup strategy in our deal sourcing to ensure access to a wealth of investment opportunities with the highest riskreward profiles”   no comments log in to comment add new comment if youre a human dont change the following field enter your name your first name please enable javascript to use this form if youre a human dont change the following field enter your name your first name please enable javascript to use this form if youre a human dont change the following field enter your name your first name please enable javascript to use this form your name subject comment  more information about text formatsplain textno html tags allowedlines and paragraphs break automatically leave this field blank news from agweb annual varmint warning posted on jul   trump may have to boost biofuel as court deals blow to oil posted on jul   trump may have to boost biofuel as court deals blow to oil  posted on jul   concentrated risk and reward posted on jul   product markets finish week with a bang posted on jul   montana wildfires have burned  acres posted on jul   you think bacon prices are high now just wait posted on jul   petes pick of the week  case ih  combine posted on jul   gmo labeling moving at snails pace posted on jul   healthcare mess makes farming even riskier posted on jul   view all articles   copyright  farm journal inc all rights reserved   w th terr suite  lenexa ks  welcome to our redesigned homepage scroll down for more stories homestead acquires sage creek vineyard  pe hub subscribe to pe hub wire join over  of your peers get the mustread email for pevc professionals delivered to your inbox daily — for free us edition daily canada edition weekly we will not send you spam and we dont share your email address with rd